bilingual.target: 货币是一种可替代的资产。

bilingual.source: Good health is an important asset for a happy life.
bilingual.target: 健康是幸福生活的重要资产。

bilingual.source: Land ownership is an important asset for farmers.
bilingual.target: 土地所有权是农民的重要资产。

bilingual.source: Patents can be a valuable asset for startups.
bilingual.target: 专利可以成为初创企业的宝贵资产。

bilingual.source: Her creativity is a significant asset to the team.
bilingual.target: 她的创造力是团队的重要资产。

bilingual.source: The house is the most valuable asset they own.
bilingual.target: 这栋房子是他们拥有的最有价值的资产。

bilingual.source: The new software is a valuable asset to our company.
bilingual.target: 这款新软件是我们公司的一项宝贵资产。

bilingual.source: The company's asset-liability ratio has decreased this year.
bilingual.target: 公司今年的资产负债率有所下降。

bilingual.source: Asset valuation is an important part of investment decisions.
bilingual.target: 资产评估是投资决策的重要部分。

bilingual.source: We need professionals to complete this asset valuation.
bilingual.target: 我们需要专业人士来完成这次资产评估。

list.abstract: asset（[ˈæset]），英语单词，词性是名词，释义为物品、人才、品质、资产等。例句：Video is a definite asset in the classroom.（录像系统是教室里必不可少的东西。） asset的复数是assets。短语有toxic asset（不良资产）、asset management（资产管理）、financial asset（金融资产）等。近义词为substance、virtue、advantage、finances。反义词为liability。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, okay. Can we just focus on the asset, please?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，好吧，我们能把重点放在资产上吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Every time we've unveiled a new asset, attendance has spiked.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每次我们推出一个新的资产的时候，入场率都会飙升。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, Asset Containment can use live ammunition in an emergency situation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 资产控制部门能在紧急状况下可以使用实弹。

yingyinNormal.en: The kind of unique asset that no government would ever admit to employing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他就是那种特别的资产，所有政府都不会承认曾经雇佣过他。

yingyinNormal.en: The powers that be, felt that he knew just a little bit too much. The asset became a liability.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那些领导者们觉得他知道得有点太多了，资产变成了负担。

yingyinNormal.en: The asset? Look, I get it. You're in charge out here. You gotta make a lot of tough decisions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 资产？听着，我懂，这里你说的算，你有很多艰难的决定要做。

yingyinNormal.en: I wonder if our fine senator has become more of a problem than asset. One that needs to be eliminated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想知道这位，好参议员，是不是已经从资产变成了负担，需要加以清理。

yingyinNormal.en: You know that I'm not at liberty to reveal the asset's genetic makeup. Modified animals are known to be unpredictable.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道我不能随意透露资产的基因成分，改良后的动物是不可预测的。

yingyinNormal.en: That doesn't mean asset development is falling behind. Our DNA excavators discover new species every year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这并不意味资产发展已经落后了，我们的基因发掘家每年都会探索出新的物种。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't need to see this person anymore. Get rid of the asset.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不需要再看到他了。处理掉他。

yingyinNormal.en: Why wouldn't you wanna have every asset available to you? Allow me to do this, Mr. President.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么不愿意用上所有的资源呢？请允许我做这件事，总统先生。

yingyinNormal.en: Would you know this fella, Alan Stonehouse? The one who... What is it? Asset stripped our firm?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你认识一个叫艾伦·斯通豪斯的人吗？这个人，他... 叫什么来着？倒卖了我们公司。

yingyinNormal.en: And I'm guessing this asset, this painting, was worth more than $20,000. Yes, it is. $8 million. Again, why?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我猜这幅画作估值超过两万美元。是的，800万，有什么问题吗？

examination_example.sentence: In a 2011 USPS case study, the agency emphasized its massive infrastructure as a "unique federal <highlight>asset</highlight>" to be called upon in a disaster or terrorist attack.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2011年美国邮政的一份案例研究中，该机构强调其庞大的基础设施是在灾难或恐怖袭击中需要调用的一份“独特的联邦资产。”

examination_example.sentence: Just lengthening that second stage of full-time work may secure the financial <highlight>assets</highlight> needed for a 100-year life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 仅仅延长全职工作这个人生第二阶段可能作为抵押使你获得活到100岁所需的金融资产。

examination_example.sentence: The Competition Commission is now to investigate whether the British Airports Authority needs to sell off some of its <highlight>assets</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 竞争委员会现在正在调查英国机场管理局是否需要出售其部分资产。
